{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel1 \b \fs32 \u55356 ?\u57272 ? Import MusicXML\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 This script imports an uncompressed MusicXML file (e.g., from Guitar Pro) into REAPER, preserving string/fret positions via MIDI channels and text events. It's designed to work seamlessly with {\b ReaTab Hero}, eliminating the need to manually reassign strings and frets after exporting MIDI.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel2 \b \fs28 Features\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Parses {\f1 <string>} and {\f1 <fret>} elements and maps string numbers to MIDI channels (string 1 \u8594 ? channel 7, etc.)\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Converts fret numbers and articulations (slides, hammer-ons, harmonics, mutes, etc.) into text or marker events\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Handles drum parts with configurable per\u8209 ?family channel mapping\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Expands repeats (forward/backward) and respects chord offsets\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Optionally imports tempo and time signature markers\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Creates separate MIDI tracks for each staff\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel2 \b \fs28 Installation\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel3 \b \fs24 Via ReaPack (recommended)\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 1.\tx360\tab In REAPER, open {\b Extensions \u8594 ? ReaPack \u8594 ? Manage Repositories}\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 2.\tx360\tab Click {\b Add} and enter: {\f1 https://github.com/kkonstantin2000/konst_reascripts/raw/master/index.xml}\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 3.\tx360\tab Click {\b OK}, then {\b Synchronize}\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 4.\tx360\tab Find the script in the Action List: {\f1 Script: Import MusicXML.lua}\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel3 \b \fs24 Manual\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Download {\f1 ImportMusicXML.lua} from the {\f1 ImportMusicXML} folder and place it in your REAPER Scripts directory.\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel2 \b \fs28 Usage\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 1.\tx360\tab Run the script from the Action List.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 2.\tx360\tab Select an uncompressed {\f1 .xml} file (MusicXML).\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 3.\tx360\tab Choose whether to import tempo/time signature markers.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 4.\tx360\tab New tracks will be created with MIDI items containing notes and text events.\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 For best results with ReaTab Hero, make sure the target track has the proper string tuning set (the script can now store tuning as track ExtState \u8211- see below).\par}
